  "title": "Education Sales Executive (Student Recruitment)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Cultivate and establish new contacts and sales leads to meet sales targets.</li>\n  <li>Ensure the achievement of monthly, quarterly, and annual quotas.</li>\n  <li>Drive student enrollment numbers and activities, including campaigns (both offline and online), open houses, information sessions, and campus visits.</li>\n  <li>Analyze competition and trends in the education sector to formulate effective sales strategies and initiatives.</li>\n  <li>Take responsibility for meeting and exceeding sales targets aligned with the institution's core competencies.</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with SSG regulations and strict adherence to the Institute’s rules and procedures.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma/Degree with at least 1 years' relevant experience preferably in the PEI education industry</li>\n  <li>Possess good assessment and experiences of education market</li>\n  <li>Possess good knowledge of the private education industry in Singapore</li>\n  <li>Possess good assessment and experiences of local cities education markets are a plus</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>\n<p>EA Personnel No: R22110981</p>\n<p>EA Personnel Name: Law Mei Fong</p>",
